      ],
      "orig": "Remove the four access screws and lift the cover clear, then inspect the ribbon cable for wear along its full length. Reseat the main connector, refit the cover, and torque the screws to the value printed on the chassis label. Restore power, run the self-test, and record the result in the maintenance log before returning the unit to service.",
      "text": "Remove the four access screws and lift the cover clear, then inspect the ribbon cable for wear along its full length. Reseat the main connector, refit the cover, and torque the screws to the value printed on the chassis label. Restore power, run the self-test, and record the result in the maintenance log before returning the unit to service."
